A disc with a slender rod attached rolls without slipping. At the instant shown, it has an angular velocity of [`\vec\omega_C = -[$omegaC]\ \textrm{rad/s}\ \hat k\ `]
and an angular acceleration of [`\vec\alpha_C = -[$alphaC]\ \textrm{rad/s}^2\ \hat k\ `]. No friction occurs between the rod and the floor. The rod has a mass
[`m_{rod} = [$mRod]\ \textrm{kg}`], [`d_1 = [$d1]\ \textrm{m}`], and [`r = [$r]\ \textrm{m}`]. A force pulls point [`\textrm{B}`] on the rod to the right with
a magnitude of [`F_B = [$FB]\ \textrm{N}`]. Determine the reaction forces [`A_x`] and [`A_y`] acting on the rod and the angular acceleration [`\vec\alpha_{AB}`] of the rod
at the instant shown.


[`\vec \alpha_{AB} = `] [_____]{"$alphaAB"} [`\hat{k}\ \textrm{rad/s}^2`]

[`A_x = `] [_____]{"$Ax"} [`\hat{i}\ \textrm{N}`]

[`A_y = `] [_____]{"$Ay"} [`\hat{j}\ \textrm{N}`]


END_PGML

